00:28:07,199 --> 00:28:09,580
Let me try that again.

586
00:28:13,721 --> 00:28:18,983
So player 11 is going to have a seat and take a little rest.

587
00:28:19,343 --> 00:28:21,184
And player 6 is just going to happen to run into him.

588
00:28:21,224 --> 00:28:26,026
These players are not in a party together, they just happen to be playing the same mission

589
00:28:26,046 --> 00:28:26,626
at the same time.

590
00:29:08,365 --> 00:29:09,646
And they run off to have adventures together.

591
00:29:09,686 --> 00:29:11,267
So this is a great moment.

592
00:29:11,287 --> 00:29:11,907
They can't talk.

593
00:29:11,987 --> 00:29:13,988
We have no, we don't turn on voice chat by default.

594
00:29:14,648 --> 00:29:15,569
They're not match made.

595
00:29:15,609 --> 00:29:16,309
They don't know each other.

596
00:29:16,329 --> 00:29:19,691
We just put them together and they have this great sort of human moment of contact.

597
00:29:21,622 --> 00:29:25,286
As it turned out, and I think pretty much every employee at Bungie can tell you the

598
00:29:25,326 --> 00:29:28,469
first moment when that system came online and we were testing an internal build and

599
00:29:28,489 --> 00:29:31,192
you just happened to run into another employee, it's like, hey, cool.

600
00:29:31,712 --> 00:29:34,475
You start following them around the environment because it's like, it works.

601
00:29:34,595 --> 00:29:35,076
It's working.

602
00:29:36,897 --> 00:29:38,998
But players were missing that moment in some of our testing,

603
00:29:39,038 --> 00:29:41,058
because they didn't realize that what they were seeing

604
00:29:41,118 --> 00:29:41,878
was another player.

605
00:29:42,419 --> 00:29:43,279
They couldn't tell the difference

606
00:29:43,399 --> 00:29:44,779
between a player and an AI.

607
00:29:45,039 --> 00:29:46,860
And this is actually a video showing an example of that.

608
00:29:47,340 --> 00:29:49,700
So what you're going to hear the moderator asking him

609
00:29:49,900 --> 00:29:52,641
as he plays is, are the players you're looking at human

610
00:29:52,721 --> 00:29:53,501
or computer-controlled?

611
00:29:54,641 --> 00:29:59,383
Computer-controlled or controlled by people?

612
00:29:59,423 --> 00:30:04,444
Computer-controlled, because this slayer just

