00:30:04,544 --> 00:30:05,464
threw a grenade that.

614
00:30:08,105 --> 00:30:08,706
I don't know yet.

615
00:30:08,746 --> 00:30:09,867
Hold on, just give me a little bit.

616
00:30:14,269 --> 00:30:16,231
And let me make it clear.

617
00:30:16,251 --> 00:30:17,131
I'm not making fun of this guy.

618
00:30:17,231 --> 00:30:18,092
He is not stupid.

619
00:30:18,692 --> 00:30:20,033
He's failing because we failed him.

620
00:30:20,093 --> 00:30:21,854
We didn't show him, we didn't give him

621
00:30:21,874 --> 00:30:23,956
the information he needed to know that those were

622
00:30:23,976 --> 00:30:25,096
real people he was looking at.

623
00:30:25,917 --> 00:30:27,978
And therefore, he didn't get that sort of magical moment

624
00:30:28,018 --> 00:30:28,999
of, hey, it's a real person.

625
00:30:29,039 --> 00:30:30,720
I'm really interacting in a living world,

626
00:30:30,980 --> 00:30:32,881
because he couldn't recognize that those were people.

627
00:30:33,882 --> 00:30:35,923
So we ended up improving the nameplates.

628
00:30:37,165 --> 00:30:39,567
to make the players look, stand out a little bit

629
00:30:39,587 --> 00:30:40,088
from the background.

630
00:30:40,128 --> 00:30:41,689
So on the left is what you saw in that video,

631
00:30:41,749 --> 00:30:43,510
and on the right is what we finally ended up with.

632
00:30:44,131 --> 00:30:45,632
To make them much more distinct from AI,

633
00:30:46,112 --> 00:30:49,194
and to make them clear that these were real players.

634
00:30:52,957 --> 00:30:53,418
Let's see.

635
00:30:53,918 --> 00:30:56,220
So we could guarantee they had that sort of magic moment.

636
00:30:57,561 --> 00:30:59,802
Another topic we looked at was directional damage indicators.

637
00:30:59,903 --> 00:31:02,444
So these were sort of, this is sort of a.

638
00:31:04,112 --> 00:31:06,294
This was almost a religious debate on the design team

639
00:31:06,594 --> 00:31:08,977
of how directional damage indicators should work.

640
00:31:09,077 --> 00:31:10,759
And so in both these images, the player

641
00:31:10,819 --> 00:31:12,601
is actually being shot from the same location.

642
00:31:13,202 --> 00:31:14,664
He's being shot from above and behind.

643
00:31:15,845 --> 00:31:17,928
And the top image is what we call

644
00:31:17,948 --> 00:31:20,571
an absolute directional damage indicator, where

645
00:31:20,811 --> 00:31:22,273
we're showing a little arrow pointing behind,

646
00:31:22,353 --> 00:31:23,955
and we're showing a flash on the top of the screen.

647
00:31:24,948 --> 00:31:28,992
The bottom image was what we called a relative directional damage indicator

648
00:31:29,492 --> 00:31:32,195
that would sort of lead you towards the person who was shooting at you.

649
00:31:32,375 --> 00:31:35,298
The idea was that you would turn towards that red flash and turn towards the arrow

650
00:31:35,598 --> 00:31:39,382
and we adjusted on the fly to aim you towards your opponent.

651
00:31:40,563 --> 00:31:43,807
And Destiny had a much faster time to kill than our previous titles.

652
00:31:44,287 --> 00:31:48,731
So we really wanted people to be good at reading the directional damage and responding to it.

653
00:31:50,251 --> 00:31:52,032
So again, this is one of those cases where the system is

654
00:31:52,072 --> 00:31:53,833
expensive to build, and we didn't want to build it

655
00:31:53,853 --> 00:31:54,933
and then decide we were wrong.

656
00:31:55,834 --> 00:31:57,855
So we built these mock-ups and asked players

657
00:31:57,895 --> 00:32:00,096
to click on a little picture of a character

658
00:32:00,676 --> 00:32:02,477
and tell us where he was being shot from.

659
00:32:02,917 --> 00:32:05,979
So for the top image, here was the heat map

660
00:32:05,999 --> 00:32:06,779
of where players clicked.

661
00:32:06,859 --> 00:32:08,420
They clicked above the character and behind him.

662
00:32:09,601 --> 00:32:11,502
But for the bottom image, pretty much everybody

663
00:32:11,542 --> 00:32:12,702
misread that and said, no, no, I'm

664
00:32:12,722 --> 00:32:13,443
being shot from the right.

665
00:32:15,803 --> 00:32:18,765
So of course, we finally ended up going with the absolute

666
00:32:18,785 --> 00:32:19,786
damage indicators at the top.

667
00:32:20,266 --> 00:32:22,728
This was almost a service we provided to the design team

668
00:32:23,288 --> 00:32:24,709
in just breaking the religious debate.

669
00:32:25,350 --> 00:32:27,571
And sort of like, OK, everyone can't agree.

670
00:32:27,651 --> 00:32:28,392
Here, here's data.

