00:32:29,132 --> 00:32:30,153
We can all move forward now.

672
00:32:32,495 --> 00:32:33,996
Destiny had a really complex UI.

673
00:32:34,656 --> 00:32:36,958
So this was the first game where Bungie made extensive use

674
00:32:36,978 --> 00:32:39,300
of eye tracking on our games.

675
00:32:42,310 --> 00:32:46,391
And mostly we primarily used it in the moment to tell what player is looking at during usability

676
00:32:46,411 --> 00:32:48,291
studies. And so I want to show you an example of that.

677
00:32:50,492 --> 00:32:53,852
So I'll warn you in advance. So this character, this player is about to

678
00:32:54,033 --> 00:32:56,853
accidentally delete a bunch of his gear while he thinks he's equipping it.

679
00:32:57,493 --> 00:33:00,554
If you've played Destiny, this is extremely painful to watch.

680
00:33:01,254 --> 00:33:01,694
I warned you.

681
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:22,042
I see some power, which might be helpful.

682
00:33:22,082 --> 00:33:26,022
You can see the material he's getting from dismantling his armor popping up in the upper right hand corner.

683
00:33:26,222 --> 00:33:29,143
Look at the green arrows.

684
00:33:29,203 --> 00:33:30,763
He already worked those in there.

685
00:33:30,783 --> 00:33:31,503
That was pretty impressive.

686
00:33:34,224 --> 00:33:34,904
Quick turnaround.

687
00:33:34,924 --> 00:33:37,744
I'm just going to try to load up.

688
00:33:41,985 --> 00:33:42,185
Okay.

