00:34:50,994 --> 00:34:51,915
but oh, that worked.

719
00:34:55,939 --> 00:34:56,079
So.

720
00:34:57,117 --> 00:34:57,718
We changed a lot.

721
00:34:57,938 --> 00:35:01,821
So among the many changes from Halo to Destiny,

722
00:35:01,881 --> 00:35:03,943
one of the minor ones was that we couldn't pause the game.

723
00:35:04,303 --> 00:35:05,704
Because Destiny is a shared world game,

724
00:35:05,784 --> 00:35:08,566
and we expect players to, it doesn't make sense

725
00:35:08,586 --> 00:35:09,987
to pause in multiplayer like that.

726
00:35:11,088 --> 00:35:14,050
And as it turns out, we used pausing

727
00:35:14,110 --> 00:35:15,912
for a whole bunch of basic logistical things

728
00:35:16,132 --> 00:35:18,234
in our research testing, from simple things

729
00:35:18,294 --> 00:35:19,795
like being able to pause and go to the bathroom.

730
00:35:20,523 --> 00:35:21,963
or telling everyone, hey, pause your game.

731
00:35:22,024 --> 00:35:23,604
We have lunch for you outside.

732
00:35:24,345 --> 00:35:25,425
And so suddenly, we couldn't do that,

733
00:35:25,465 --> 00:35:26,525
because the game doesn't pause.

734
00:35:27,786 --> 00:35:29,387
But one of things we also used pausing for

735
00:35:29,647 --> 00:35:31,568
was giving feedback while people were playing.

736
00:35:31,808 --> 00:35:33,549
As they were playing along in a campaign mission,

737
00:35:33,709 --> 00:35:36,410
we'd pop up a little dialogue saying, how are you doing?

738
00:35:37,070 --> 00:35:39,791
And they could say, I'm bored, I'm fine, I'm frustrated,

739
00:35:39,811 --> 00:35:41,612
I'm lost, whatever, as they were playing.

740
00:35:41,632 --> 00:35:44,553
And then we'd pause the game behind that menu as it came up.

741
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:48,822
And of course in Destiny, if we'd done that, players would die.

